<div class="column medium">
		<h2>Automatic backup to Google Drive, Amazon S3, Azure Storage, FTP, Tape, NAS, etc.</h2>
		<p class="text">Iperius allows you to integrate the MySQL backup with many useful options: in fact, you can automatically transfer the backup files to any mass storage device (like NAS or tape drives) or you can make remote backups to FTP servers, Google Drive, Amazon S3, Azure Storage, etc. Thanks to these powerful features, together with the possibility to keep multiple copies of your backups, Iperius is one of the most flexible and complete software to protect MySQL databases.</p>
</div>
<div class="column medium last">
		<h2>One license, no limitation</h2>
		<p class="text">Iperius Backup is the most affordable software to back up MySQL databases and MariaDB, because in a single, lightweight and portable software you have unlimited possibilities in backup configuration, and you have no limitation in the number of databases or servers. You can run unlimited backup tasks, even in parallel mode, of local or remote databases.</p>
</div>
                          
<div class="clearfix">
</div>

<div class="column medium">
		<h2>Compatible with all versions of MySQL and MariaDB</h2>
		<p class="text">Iperius Backup works with all versions of MySQL (5.x, 4.x, 3.23) and MariaDB, and can back up databases of any size with high performances, without needing any prerequisite. The backups files created by Iperius are in the standard format of MySQL, hence perfectly readable by any other program and always compatible.</p>
</div>
<div class="column medium last">
		<h2>Compression, AES encryption, verification, reports by email</h2>
		<p class="text">Iperius is not a simple database backup program, since it comes with many additional and useful features, like zip compression, advanced verification, AES encryption, and the possibility to keep multiple backup copies of each database. In addition, you have detailed email notification options, to be always informed about the backup result.</p>
